   "source": [
    "# Renewal theory"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "c2e1b61a-aff1-47ca-8a6d-a249db479588",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from relife import Weibull, RenewalProcess"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "9d4e029c-ed3c-4eb1-a676-5f2efb016bb9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Choix de la distribution des temps inter-arrivées\n",
    "distrib = Weibull(5, 0.03)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Création du processus de renouvellement associé\n",
    "rp = RenewalProcess(distrib)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot de la fonction de renouvellement qui correspond au nombre moyen de défaillance au cours du temps, ici dans une stratégie run to failure\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, 150, num=5000)\n",
    "plt.plot(t, rp.renewal_function(t), label=\"Fonction de renouvellement\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"t\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "b38da094-223d-48b6-b18e-4d486022e15f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from relife.renewal import renewal_equation_solver\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def f(x):\n",
    "    return distrib.cdf(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, 150, num=100)\n",
    "tm = (t[1:] + t[:-1]) / 2\n",
    "m = renewal_equation_solver(t, distrib, f)\n",
    "plt.plot(t, m)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "ec197179-f83a-47d1-b172-6e99878b87a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Plot de la densité de renouvellement qui correspond au nombre moyen de défaillance par unité de temps, au cours du temps.\n",
    "plt.plot(t, rp.renewal_density(t), label=\"Densité de renouvellement\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"t\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "071842db-211b-46e6-aaa9-3a2e99679ba1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calcul de la distribution des âges à l'équilibre. A temps suffisament long, la varariance des durées de vie \"étale\" les défaillance dans le temps\n",
    "# ce qui aboutit à une stabilisation du rythme d'apparition des défaillances au cours du temps. Lorsque ce régime stationnaire est atteint,\n",
    "# la population d'actifs a une distribution d'âge qui ne varie plus au cours du temps : c'est la distribution d'âges à l'équilibre.\n",
    "from relife.fiability import EquilibriumDistribution\n",
    "\n",
    "eq_distrib = EquilibriumDistribution(distrib)\n",
    "\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, 75, num=1000)\n",
    "plt.plot(t, eq_distrib.pdf(t), label=\"Distribution des âges des actifs à l'équilibre\")\n",
    "plt.plot(t, distrib.pdf(t), label=\"Distribution des durées de vie des actifs\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"t\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Densité\")\n",
    "plt.legend(loc=\"upper right\")\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, 0.07)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "8e233b45-743f-4125-9372-ac98cd9824e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "end_time = 1000\n",
    "nb_samples = 5000\n",
    "\n",
    "renewal_sample = rp.sample(nb_samples, end_time)\n",
    "age_eq = np.zeros(nb_samples)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(nb_samples):\n",
    "    age_eq[i] = (\n",
    "        end_time - renewal_sample.event_times[renewal_sample.samples_index == i][-1]\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, np.max(age_eq), num=1000)\n",
    "plt.hist(age_eq, density=True, label=\"Histogramme des âges des actifs à temps long\")\n",
    "plt.plot(t, eq_distrib.pdf(t), label=\"Distribution théorique des âges à l'équilibre\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Ages\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Densité\")\n",
    "plt.ylim((0, 0.04))\n",
    "plt.legend(loc=\"upper right\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "3efebbd5-6809-45be-b551-81d48e864a77",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "end_time = 1000\n",
    "nb_samples = 5000\n",
    "\n",
    "renewal_sample = rp.sample(nb_samples, end_time)\n",
    "age_eq = np.zeros(nb_samples)\n",
    "\n",
    "for sample, asset, event_times, lifetimes, events in renewal_sample.iter():\n",
    "    age_eq[sample] = end_time - event_times[-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, np.max(age_eq), num=1000)\n",
    "plt.hist(age_eq, density=True, label=\"Histogramme des âges des actifs à temps long\")\n",
    "plt.plot(t, eq_distrib.pdf(t), label=\"Distribution théorique des âges à l'équilibre\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Ages\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Densité\")\n",
    "plt.ylim((0, 0.04))\n",
    "plt.legend(loc=\"upper right\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
